Student_Growth_Description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between Spring 2015 and Spring 2016. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that started with similar scores in 2015. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2016. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: This school is “Well-Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a very strong culture and climate, suggesting the school is set up for success. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate, visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2016 .

Student_Growth_Description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between Spring 2015 and Spring 2016. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that started with similar scores in 2015. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2016. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.

It nearly meets the goals and priorities outlined in the CPS Arts Education Plan, including Staffing & Instruction, Partnerships, Community & Culture, and Budget & Planning. To learn more, visit  www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification .
School_Survey_Rating_Description: This school is “Moderately Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has both strengths and weaknesses in their culture and climate. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2016 .
Supportive_School_Award_Desc: This school is in the process of being reviewed for its implementation of supports for social and emotional learning (SEL) and will receive a rating next year. For information about this new certification, visit  www.cps.edu/sel

Student_Growth_Description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between Spring 2015 and Spring 2016. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that started with similar scores in 2015. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2016. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: This school is “Well-Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a very strong culture and climate, suggesting the school is set up for success. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate, visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2016 .

This growth is measured based on an expected ACT score based on their ISAT score.
Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2016. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.

Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2016. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: This school is “Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a strong culture and climate with only a few areas for improvement. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2016 .
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  www.cps.edu/healthycps .

Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2016. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: This school is “Well-Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a very strong culture and climate, suggesting the school is set up for success. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate, visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2016 .
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  www.cps.edu/healthycps .
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school is Excelling in the arts. It meets the goals and priorities outlined in the CPS Arts Education Plan, including Staffing & Instruction, Partnerships, Community & Culture, and Budget & Planning. To learn more, visit  www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification .

For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate, visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2016 .

Supportive_School_Award_Desc: This school is in the process of being reviewed for its implementation of supports for social and emotional learning (SEL) and will receive a rating next year. For information about this new certification, visit  www.cps.edu/sel

Student_Growth_Description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between students' 8th grade ISAT score (Spring 2013) and 11th grade ACT score (Spring 2016). This growth is measured based on an expected ACT score based on their ISAT score.
Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2016. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: This school is “Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a strong culture and climate with only a few areas for improvement. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2016 .

Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2016. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: This school is “Well-Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a very strong culture and climate, suggesting the school is set up for success. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate, visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2016 .
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school achieved Healthy CPS and demonstrates a commitment to a healthy learning environment. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  www.cps.edu/healthycps .
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school is Strong in the arts. It nearly meets the goals and priorities outlined in the CPS Arts Education Plan, including Staffing & Instruction, Partnerships, Community & Culture, and Budget & Planning. To learn more, visit  www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification .

Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2016. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: This school is “Well-Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a very strong culture and climate, suggesting the school is set up for success. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate, visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2016 .
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  www.cps.edu/healthycps .
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school is Excelling in the arts. It meets the goals and priorities outlined in the CPS Arts Education Plan, including Staffing & Instruction, Partnerships, Community & Culture, and Budget & Planning. To learn more, visit  www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification .

Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2016. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: This school is “Well-Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a very strong culture and climate, suggesting the school is set up for success. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate, visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2016 .
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  www.cps.edu/healthycps .
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school is Excelling in the arts. It meets the goals and priorities outlined in the CPS Arts Education Plan, including Staffing & Instruction, Partnerships, Community & Culture, and Budget & Planning. To learn more, visit  www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification .

Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2016. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: This school is “Well-Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a very strong culture and climate, suggesting the school is set up for success. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate, visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2016 .
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  www.cps.edu/healthycps .
